#, fuzzy
#~| msgid ""
#~| "Having specified the header this section explains how the indentation "
#~| "scripting itself works. The basic skeleton of the body looks like this: "
#~| "<programlisting>\n"
#~| "triggerCharacters = \"{}/:;\";\n"
#~| "function indent(line, indentWidth, ch)\n"
#~| "{\n"
#~| "    // called for each newline (ch == '\\n') and all characters "
#~| "specified in\n"
#~| "    // the global variable triggerCharacters. When calling "
#~| "<menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Align</guimenuitem></"
#~| "menuchoice>\n"
#~| "    // the variable ch is empty, i.e. ch == ''.\n"
#~| "    //\n"
#~| "    // see also: Scripting API\n"
#~| "    return -2;\n"
#~| "}\n"
#~| "</programlisting> The function <function>indent()</function> has three "
#~| "parameters: <itemizedlist> <listitem><para><literal>line</literal>: the "
#~| "line that has to be indented</para></listitem> "
#~| "<listitem><para><literal>indentWidth</literal>: the indentation width in "
#~| "amount of spaces</para></listitem> <listitem><para><literal>ch</"
#~| "literal>: either a newline character (<literal>ch == '\\n'</literal>), "
#~| "the trigger character specified in <literal>triggerCharacters</literal> "
#~| "or empty if the user invoked the action <menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</"
#~| "guimenu><guimenuitem>Align</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.</para></listitem> "
#~| "</itemizedlist> The return value of the <function>indent()</function> "
#~| "function specifies how the line will be indented. If the return value is "
#~| "a simple integer number, it is interpreted as follows: <itemizedlist> "
#~| "<listitem><para>return value <literal>-2</literal>: do nothing</para></"
#~| "listitem> <listitem><para>return value <literal>-1</literal>: keep "
#~| "indentation (searches for previous non-blank line)</para></listitem> "
#~| "<listitem><para>return value <literal> 0</literal>: numbers &gt;= 0 "
#~| "specify the indentation depth in spaces</para></listitem> </"
#~| "itemizedlist> Alternatively, an array of two elements can be returned: "
#~| "<itemizedlist> <listitem><para><literal>return [ indent, align ];</"
#~| "literal></para></listitem> </itemizedlist> In this case, the first "
#~| "element is the indentation depth like above with the same meaning of the "
#~| "special values. However, the second element is an absolute value "
#~| "representing a column for <quote>alignment</quote>. If this value is "
#~| "higher than the indent value, the difference represents a number of "
#~| "spaces to be added after the indentation of the first parameter. "
#~| "Otherwise, the second number is ignored. Using tabs and spaces for "
#~| "indentation is often referred to as <quote>mixed mode</quote>."
#~ msgid ""
#~ "Having specified the header this section explains how the indentation "
#~ "scripting itself works. The basic skeleton of the body looks like this: "
#~ "<programlisting>\n"
#~ "// required katepart js libraries, e.g. range.js if you use Range\n"
#~ "require (\"range.js\");\n"
#~ "  \n"
#~ "triggerCharacters = \"{}/:;\";\n"
#~ "function indent(line, indentWidth, ch)\n"
#~ "{\n"
#~ "    // called for each newline (ch == '\\n') and all characters specified "
#~ "in\n"
#~ "    // the global variable triggerCharacters. When calling "
#~ "<menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Align</guimenuitem></"
#~ "menuchoice>\n"
#~ "    // the variable ch is empty, i.e. ch == ''.\n"
#~ "    //\n"
#~ "    // see also: Scripting API\n"
#~ "    return -2;\n"
#~ "}\n"
#~ "</programlisting> The function <function>indent()</function> has three "
#~ "parameters: <itemizedlist> <listitem><para><literal>line</literal>: the "
#~ "line that has to be indented</para></listitem> "
#~ "<listitem><para><literal>indentWidth</literal>: the indentation width in "
#~ "number of spaces</para></listitem> <listitem><para><literal>ch</literal>: "
#~ "either a newline character (<literal>ch == '\\n'</literal>), the trigger "
#~ "character specified in <literal>triggerCharacters</literal> or empty if "
#~ "the user invoked the action <menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</"
#~ "guimenu><guimenuitem>Align</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.</para></listitem> "
#~ "</itemizedlist> The return value of the <function>indent()</function> "
#~ "function specifies how the line will be indented. If the return value is "
#~ "a simple integer number, it is interpreted as follows: <itemizedlist> "
#~ "<listitem><para>return value <literal>-2</literal>: do nothing</para></"
#~ "listitem> <listitem><para>return value <literal>-1</literal>: keep "
#~ "indentation (searches for previous non-blank line)</para></listitem> "
#~ "<listitem><para>return value <literal> 0</literal>: numbers &gt;= 0 "
#~ "specify the indentation depth in spaces</para></listitem> </itemizedlist> "
#~ "Alternatively, an array of two elements can be returned: <itemizedlist> "
#~ "<listitem><para><literal>return [ indent, align ];</literal></para></"
#~ "listitem> </itemizedlist> In this case, the first element is the "
#~ "indentation depth as above with the same meaning of the special values. "
#~ "However, the second element is an absolute value representing a column "
#~ "for <quote>alignment</quote>. If this value is higher than the indent "
#~ "value, the difference represents a number of spaces to be added after the "
#~ "indentation of the first parameter. Otherwise, the second number is "
#~ "ignored. Using tabs and spaces for indentation is often referred to as "
#~ "<quote>mixed mode</quote>."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Unha vez escrita a cabeceira, é hora de escribir o código que determina a "
#~ "lóxica do script de sangrado. O esqueleto básico do corpo ten o seguinte "
#~ "aspecto: <programlisting>\n"
#~ "triggerCharacters = \"{}/:;\";\n"
#~ "function indent(line, indentWidth, ch)\n"
#~ "{\n"
#~ "    // Esta función execútase para cada nova liña (ch == '\\n') e para\n"
#~ "    // todos os caracteres indicados na variábel global "
#~ "triggerCharacters.\n"
#~ "    // Cando se executa <menuchoice><guimenu>Utilidades</"
#~ "guimenu><guimenuitem>Aliñar</guimenuitem></menuchoice>\n"
#~ "    // o parámetro ch chega baleiro, é dicir, ch == ''.\n"
#~ "    //     // Vexa tamén a información da sección «API para scripts», "
#~ "máis abaixo.    return -2;\n"
#~ "}\n"
#~ "</programlisting>  A función <function>indent()</function> recibe tres "
#~ "parámetros: <itemizedlist>   <listitem><para><literal>line</literal>. A "
#~ "liña cuxo sangrado debe axustarse.</para></listitem>   "
#~ "<listitem><para><literal>indentWidth</literal>. A anchura do sangrado, "
#~ "medida en cantidade de espazos.</para></listitem>   "
#~ "<listitem><para><literal>ch</literal>. Un carácter de salto de liña "
#~ "(<literal>ch == '\\n'</literal>), o carácter disparador indicado en "
#~ "<literal>triggerCharacters</literal> ou unha cadea baleira se o usuario "
#~ "executou a acción <menuchoice><guimenu>Utilidades</"
#~ "guimenu><guimenuitem>Aliñar</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.</para></listitem> "
#~ "</itemizedlist>  O valor que devolva a función <function>indent()</"
#~ "function> determinará o sangrado da liña. De tratarse dun número enteiro, "
#~ "interpretarase da seguinte maneira: <itemizedlist>   "
#~ "<listitem><para><literal>-2</literal>. Non facer nada.</para></"
#~ "listitem>   <listitem><para><literal>-1</literal>. Manter o sangrado da "
#~ "primeira liña non baleira anterior á actual.</para></listitem>   "
#~ "<listitem><para><literal> 0</literal>. Os números positivos, incluído o "
#~ "0, indican o nivel de sangrado a aplicar á liña, en espazos.</para></"
#~ "listitem> </itemizedlist> En vez dun enteiro, é posíbel devolver unha "
#~ "matriz de dous elementos: <itemizedlist>   "
#~ "<listitem><para><literal>[ sangrado, aliñación ];</literal></para></"
#~ "listitem> </itemizedlist> Neste caso, o primeiro elemento correspóndese "
#~ "co nivel de sangrado, igual que cando se devolve un número enteiro. Pola "
#~ "outra banda, o segundo elemento é un valor absoluto que representa a "
#~ "columna para a <quote>aliñación</quote>. Se o valor é superior ao valor "
#~ "de sangrado, a diferencia representa un número de espazos a engadir tras "
#~ "o sangrado do primeiro parámetro (o <quote>sangrado</quote>). En caso "
#~ "contrario, este segundo número ignorarase. Ao uso de tabulacións e "
#~ "espazos para o sangrado adoita chamárselle <quote>modo mixto</quote>."

#~ msgid ""
